messages.message:
_*Weekly Testing Tips + Tricks*_!!! :blob-dab: Week 6!
If you’re running tests locally, try `--onlyChanged` for only running tests affected by local changes (or `--changedSince master` if you’ve already made some commits)!
Also an extension of @William Helmrath’s tip on `test.only`: this also works on `describe` so you can run `describe.only` to run only a specific group of tests!
https://jestjs.io/docs/api#describeonlyname-fn
I think I totally missed week 5 :disappointed: I will try to add one soon!
